{
  "name": "Windswept Adornments",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A set of 3 spirally symbols that impart the airy nature of wind upon the individual adorned by them. Two of them are earrings accompanied by the tail feathers of a bird. The third adornment is loose and can be tucked away in a pocket.</p><p>While attuned to this set of three adornments they each provide a unique benefit.</p><ul><li>You and everything you are wearing grows lighter when you inhale. You can hold your breath at any point to both lighten the armor and quiet its clattering, negating the normal disadvantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks imposed by certain armors.</li><li>You can hold your breath as a <strong>Reaction</strong> to cast the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.n5VyKMuilCXJRuXw]{Feather Fall}spell, targeting only yourself, at will.</li><li>As a <strong>Bonus</strong> action you can jump a number of feet equal to 5 x your <strong>proficiency bonus</strong>, without provoking opportunity attacks. You can use this trait only if your speed is greater than 0. This jump distance is separate from your movement distance. You can jump in this way a number of times equal to your <strong>proficiency bonus</strong>, and regain all expended uses at dawn.</li></ul><p><strong>Recharge:</strong> The Windswept Adornments regains all expended charges at Dawn.</p><p><strong>Special: </strong>These items are considered jewelry for the purpose of Locus affixing.</p>",
